In one time step of the simulation, every individual is selected once, and their states are attempted for a possible update. The updates are done in a parallel updating scheme, such that a given update comes into effect in the following time step. If an individual is in the susceptible state and one of the eight neighbors is infected, then the susceptible individual can be infected with probability p. If an infected individual has remained in that state for \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
